          <li><strong>Content optimization</strong> — real-time scoring as you write or edit</li>
          <li><strong>Export &amp; partial publishing</strong> — WordPress plugin, doc export, basic API</li>
        </ol>

        <h2 id="features">Outranking features — the full 2026 walkthrough</h2>

        <h3>1. SERP research + brief builder</h3>
        <p>Enter a keyword. Outranking pulls the top 10 results, surfaces semantic terms, and proposes an outline. The brief output is solid — competitive with Frase for assignment-brief workflows. Useful even if you don't use the AI writer.</p>

        <h3>2. AI writer</h3>
        <p>Drafts paragraphs and full sections based on your outline. Quality is acceptable for first drafts; voice and accuracy still need human editing. The "one-click article" workflow exists but produces drafts you should always review before publishing.</p>

        <h3>3. Content optimization scoring</h3>
        <p>Real-time Content Score against the top 10 SERP results. Similar to Surfer and Frase. Less polished UI than Surfer, more integrated with the writing workflow than Frase.</p>

        <h3>4. Templates &amp; workflows</h3>
        <p>Pre-built templates for product pages, listicles, comparison articles, glossary entries. Speed up first-draft time on common formats.</p>

        <h3>5. WordPress publishing</h3>
        <p>Direct push to WordPress via plugin. Not as broad as Outrank.so's multi-CMS coverage. No Webflow, Ghost, or Shopify integrations yet.</p>

